-- Harmony Gold Says Phakisa Mine Remains Closed After Explosion Kills Four
-- Carli Lourens
-- 2010-06-28T06:08:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/harmony-gold-says-phakisa-mine-remains-closed-after-explosion-kills-four.html

          
          
             Harmony Gold Mining Co. said its
Phakisa mine in South Africa remains closed after an explosion
on June 24 killed four workers.  
 The fourth worker died later of his wounds, Marian van der
Walt, a company spokeswoman, said in an interview today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        